This computer science program, known as PLM, has been used to develop assembly chains in factories around the world, power plants and high-precision instruments.
The aim is to reproduce or simulate a product or process faithfully before it is actually built, in order to avoid errors and unnecessary costs.
PLM has facilitated the development of Canon cameras, Sukhoi aircraft and Nissan’s most famous commercial vehicles.
