Their market share for private customers is 3.5 percent, while business customers account for more than 10 percent.
Another principle of the 2011-2013 business plan is the increase in productivity, i.e. austerity, cost reduction. The challenges the bank faces will be presented together with the annual financial report.
Few banks dare to set and publish targets in these difficult times, as the financial crisis has disrupted all the plans of the banks around the world.
Sabadell will complete this year’s Optima guidance plan, which was initially designed for three years, but which has been extended by one financial year as a result of the market situation.
The customers who will leave the savings banks are the main objective of the bank.
