"Pakistan must hire strictly faithful personnel to guard the nuclear facilities; because of the low level of education and culture, extremist organizations have more opportunities to recluse people working on nuclear or missile programs," said Yuri Korolev, an expert at the Russian Foreign Ministry, in a meeting with his North American counterparts.
